      "SummaryText": "ocedure, and emergency response.\n\n4. 5-Year accident History\n\nNo RMP process related accidents have occurred at this facility within the last five years.\n\n5. Emergency Response program\n\nThe facility's emergency response is outlined in their specific Emergency Action and Emergency Response Plans which includes responding to chlorine and sulfur dioxide leaks only. The Harcros team members that handle the RMP chemicals are HAZWOPER and CHLOREP trained. Harcros works closely with our suppliers, customers, public responders, and the Chlorine Institute to continuously improve our emergency response capabilities.\n\n6. Planned changes to improve safety\n\nHarcros continues to participate in the Chlorine Institute's and the National Association of Chemical Distributor's programs, and although no specific safety improvements are scheduled at this time, we continue to improve our operations in accordance with Responsible Distribution Guidelines. Frequent site inspections are completed in order to identify any safety improvements. We are planning to replace our manual front gate with a badge-access, automatic gate by the end of 2024."
