    {
      "ESSeqNum": 0,
      "FacilityID": 1000114036,
      "SummaryText": "Bessemer - RMP Executive Summary\n\nThe following is a summary of the six elements of the Risk Management Program as part of our 5-year update that has been implemented at the Harcros facility located at 1496 Highway 150, Bessemer, AL 35022. The changes in this RMP update include the recently updated PHA, which has formatting changes, and improved FMEA, and a more detailed human factors review.  The RMP also includes several updated dates and executive summary. \n\n1. Accidental release prevention and emergency response policies\n\nOur emergency response program is based upon The Chlorine Institute Pamphlet 64, Emergency Response Plans for Chlorine Facilities. The emergency response plan includes procedures for notification of the local fire authority and notification of our immediate neighbors.\n\n2. Stationary source and regulated substances handled\n\nThe facility handles two chemicals above the RMP threshold limits: Chlorine and Sulfur Dioxide. They are both stored in 150 lb and ton cylinders. Neither chemical is packaged or used at this facility.\n\n3. Accidental release prevention program\n\nDue to the storage and handling of Chlorine and Sulfur Dioxide, this site falls under RMP Program Level 3 which includes the elements of OSHA\u0092s Process Safety Management Program (Process Safety Information, Process Hazard Analysis, Operating Procedures, Training, Mechanical Integrity, Management of Change, Pre-startup Safety Reviews, compliance audit, Incident Investigation, Employee Participation, Hot Work, and Contractor Safety) . An original Process Hazard Analysis was conducted and those corrective actions have been closed. The facility revalidated the Process Hazard Analysis in 2023 and all corrective actions are scheduled to be completed by the end of June, 2024. The accidental release prevention program includes but not limited to access control and security of the site; checking prepackage cylinders that cross their docks for tampering and damage as per the standard operating pr"
